# 6. Admin Dashboard Architecture

## Introduction

The Admin Dashboard serves as the central management system for Moksha Gaya. It enables administrators, coordinators, and operational staff to manage customer enquiries, bookings, services, content, and business operations from a single platform.

The dashboard is designed to improve efficiency, increase visibility into business operations, and support future growth.

---

# Dashboard Objectives

The Admin Dashboard should:

### Centralize Operations

Provide a single interface for managing all business activities.

---

### Improve Efficiency

Reduce manual work and simplify workflows.

---

### Increase Visibility

Provide real-time insights into bookings, leads, and operations.

---

### Support Growth

Allow new services, locations, and team members to be added easily.

---

# Dashboard Homepage

The main dashboard should provide a quick overview of business activity.

---

## Key Metrics

### Total Leads

Number of enquiries received.

---

### Active Bookings

Current confirmed bookings.

---

### Completed Services

Successfully completed rituals.

---

### Pending Follow-Ups

Leads requiring coordinator action.

---

### Monthly Enquiries

Total enquiries received during the month.

---

### Conversion Rate

Percentage of enquiries converted into bookings.

---

# Lead Management Module

## Purpose

Manage customer enquiries and booking requests.

---

## Features

### View Leads

List all customer enquiries.

