# 7. Lead Management & CRM Workflow

## Introduction

The Lead Management and CRM Workflow defines how customer enquiries are captured, managed, tracked, and converted into confirmed bookings.

The objective is to ensure that every lead receives timely attention, structured follow-up, and professional communication throughout the customer journey.

A well-defined CRM process helps improve conversion rates, customer satisfaction, operational efficiency, and long-term business growth.

---

# CRM Objectives

The CRM system should:

### Capture Every Enquiry

No customer enquiry should be lost.

---

### Improve Follow-Ups

Ensure consistent communication.

---

### Increase Conversions

Convert more enquiries into confirmed bookings.

---

### Maintain Customer History

Store complete customer interaction records.

---

### Support Long-Term Relationships

Encourage repeat bookings and referrals.

---

# Lead Sources

Leads may originate from multiple channels.

### Website Enquiry Forms

Primary source of leads.

---

### WhatsApp

Direct customer enquiries.

---

### Phone Calls

Inbound customer calls.

---

### Email Enquiries

Customer communication via email.

---

### Social Media

Facebook, Instagram, YouTube, etc.

---

### Referral Sources

Existing customers and partner referrals.

---

# Lead Lifecycle

Every lead should move through a structured workflow.

---

## Stage 1: New Lead

### Description

Customer submits an enquiry.

### System Actions

* Generate Lead ID
* Store customer information
* Notify administrator
* Notify assigned coordinator

### Status

New Lead

---

## Stage 2: Contact Attempted

### Description

Coordinator initiates communication.

### Actions

* Phone call
* WhatsApp message
* Email communication

### Status

Contact Attempted

---

## Stage 3: Consultation Completed

### Description

Customer requirements have been discussed.

### Information Collected

* Ritual requirements
* Travel requirements
* Package preference
* Scheduling preferences

### Status

Consultation Completed

---

## Stage 4: Quotation Shared

### Description

Service proposal and pricing have been communicated.

### Information Shared

* Recommended package
* Pricing
* Inclusions
* Service schedule

### Status

Quotation Shared

---

## Stage 5: Follow-Up

### Description

Coordinator follows up regarding the proposal.

### Objective

Address questions and encourage booking confirmation.

### Status

Follow-Up

---

## Stage 6: Booking Confirmed

### Description

Customer agrees to proceed.

### Actions

* Finalize arrangements
* Assign resources
* Schedule services

### Status

Confirmed

---

## Stage 7: Service Delivery

### Description

Services are actively being delivered.

### Status

In Progress

---

## Stage 8: Service Completed

### Description

Rituals and related services have been completed.

### Actions

* Collect feedback
* Request testimonial
* Archive records

### Status

Completed

---

## Stage 9: Closed

### Description

Customer journey completed.

### Status

Closed

---

# Follow-Up Strategy

Effective follow-up significantly improves conversion rates.

---

## First Follow-Up

Timing:

Within 24 hours of enquiry submission.

Objective:

Establish contact and understand requirements.

---

## Second Follow-Up

Timing:

1–2 days after consultation.

Objective:

Address customer concerns.

---

## Third Follow-Up

Timing:

2–3 days after quotation.

Objective:

Encourage booking decision.

---

## Final Follow-Up

Timing:

Before lead closure.

Objective:

Confirm customer decision.

---

# Customer Communication Standards

Every interaction should be:

### Professional

Maintain respectful communication.

---

### Transparent

Provide accurate information.

---

### Compassionate

Recognize the emotional nature of spiritual services.

---

### Responsive

Respond promptly to enquiries.

---

### Consistent

Ensure communication quality across all channels.

---

# CRM Customer Profile

Each customer profile should contain:

### Personal Information

* Name
* Mobile Number
* Email Address
* City
* State
* Country

---

### Service Information

* Service Requested
* Preferred Date
* Package Preference

---

### Communication History

* Calls
* WhatsApp Messages
* Emails
* Notes

---

### Booking History

* Previous Services
* Previous Enquiries
* Previous Payments

---

# Lead Scoring System

Future versions may prioritize leads based on:

### Service Type

High-value services receive higher priority.

---

### Urgency

Near-term requirements receive higher priority.

---

### Customer Profile

Premium and repeat customers may receive priority handling.

---

# Coordinator Responsibilities

Coordinators should:

### Review New Leads

Daily.

---

### Maintain Accurate Records

Update CRM notes regularly.

---

### Conduct Follow-Ups

According to defined schedules.

---

### Update Lead Statuses

Maintain accurate pipeline visibility.

---

### Escalate Special Cases

When required.

---

# CRM Reports

The CRM should generate:

### Lead Source Report

Track lead origins.

---

### Conversion Report

Track enquiry-to-booking performance.

---

### Follow-Up Report

Monitor coordinator activity.

---

### Customer Retention Report

Track repeat customers.

---

### Monthly CRM Performance Report

Evaluate overall CRM effectiveness.

---

# Key CRM Metrics

### Lead Volume

Total enquiries received.

---

### Conversion Rate

Percentage of leads converted into bookings.

---

### Average Response Time

Time taken to contact new leads.

---

### Follow-Up Completion Rate

Percentage of scheduled follow-ups completed.

---

### Customer Satisfaction

Post-service feedback score.

---

# Future CRM Enhancements

Future versions may include:

### Automated Follow-Ups

### WhatsApp Integration

### Email Automation

### AI Lead Prioritization

### Customer Dashboard Integration

### Loyalty Program Management

---

# Conclusion

The CRM workflow serves as the operational engine of Moksha Gaya. By implementing structured lead management, timely communication, and consistent follow-up processes, the company can improve customer satisfaction, increase booking conversions, and build long-term relationships with devotees.


