# 9. Database Architecture & Data Model

## Introduction

The Moksha Gaya platform requires a scalable, secure, and maintainable database architecture capable of supporting customer enquiries, bookings, services, content management, reporting, and future expansion.

The database design should follow a modular structure that allows additional services, locations, and features to be added without major architectural changes.

The proposed database will use PostgreSQL as the primary database engine and Prisma ORM as the data access layer.

---

# Database Design Principles

The database architecture should be:

### Scalable

Support future business growth.

---

### Secure

Protect customer and operational data.

---

### Maintainable

Allow easy updates and modifications.

---

### Performant

Provide fast response times.

---

### Extensible

Support future features and integrations.

---

# Core Entities

The platform consists of the following primary entities:

### Users

### Customers

### Leads

### Bookings

### Services

### Packages

### Testimonials

### Blog Articles

### Gallery Items

### Sacred Places

### Notifications

### Activity Logs

---

